Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, boil a full #kettle{}.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{110%grams} and crumble the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%grams}, then add both to a #medium bowl{}.

Pop the @Baby Spinach{150%grams} into a #colander{} in your sink. Pour over the
boiling water from your kettle until wilted and piping hot. Once wilted, squeeze
out all of the excess water from the spinach with the back of a #spoon{}.

Stir the spinach, @Red Pepper Chilli Jelly{37%grams} and @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%grams}
into the cheese. Mix well until combined, then season with pepper.

Unroll the @Filo Pastry Sheets{4}(2 per person) and fold each sheet in half widthways
to create a rectangle.

Spoon the mixture along one end of each rectangle, leaving a 2cm border around
the bottom 3 edges.

Neatly fold both lengthway sides over the filling, then tightly roll them up to
enclose the filling.

Transfer your sigara böreği, seam side down onto a lined, large baking tray.

Brush with a little oil, sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%grams},
then bake on the top shelf until golden brown, ~{10-15%minutes}.

== Rocket Salad ==

Whilst the sigara böreği bake, in a medium bowl, combine the
@Cider Vinegar{15%milliliter}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the
dressing. Season with salt and pepper.

Just before everything's ready, toss the @Wild Rocket{40%grams} through the dressing.

== To Serve ==

Share the spanakopita inspired sigara böreği between your plates.

Serve the rocket salad and chips alongside with @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} for dipping.

Finish by drizzling @Honey{2%tbsp} over the sigara böreği.

> Enjoy!

> A recipe that's enjoyed across the Balkans, spanakopita consists of a crumbly
> white cheese and spinach filling, stuffed between layers of pastry. Here, we're
> making mini rolls inspired by Turkish sigara böreği for a more handheld experience!